tor><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132519356,imgsize-280222.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[After years of living in a trailer, a couple self-built their 3,600-square-foot home for $410K]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132514450.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Allison Brown and her husband spent six years living in a 1,500-square-foot trailer in South Dakota to keep their housing costs low and save money. Those savings later helped them build their own 3,600-square-foot home for about $410,000 by managing the project themselves. They also turned their old trailer into an Airbnb, creating an additoinal source of income.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/real-estate/after-years-of-living-in-a-trailer-a-couple-self-built-their-3600-square-foot-dream-home-for-410k-saving-up-to-350k-after-contractors-quoted-as-much-as-800k/articleshow/132514450.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/real-estate/after-years-of-living-in-a-trailer-a-couple-self-built-their-3600-square-foot-dream-home-for-410k-saving-up-to-350k-after-contractors-quoted-as-much-as-800k/articleshow/132514450.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T20:04:42+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Real Estate Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132515418,imgsize-126884.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Father saved for years so that I could study in America but...: Woman's 'American Dream' turns into 'Make in India']]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132519261.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/father-saved-for-years-so-that-i-could-study-in-america-but-womans-american-dream-turns-into-make-in-india/articleshow/132519261.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/father-saved-for-years-so-that-i-could-study-in-america-but-womans-american-dream-turns-into-make-in-india/articleshow/132519261.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T21:27:45+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132519317,imgsize-94648.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[How wild snapdragons tune colors for bees]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132518533.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Wild snapdragons showcase an impressive ability to adjust their petal colors with the help of seven genes, aimed at attracting bees. These vibrant flowers utilize this precise color calibration as visual cues for their pollinators. Researchers discovered that these genetic variations create subtle yet significant differences, which are critical for survival in narrow hybrid zones where less effective colors are less likely to thrive.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/how-wild-snapdragons-fine-tune-their-shades-to-attract-bees-even-the-smallest-change-decide-which-genes-survive/articleshow/132518533.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/how-wild-snapdragons-fine-tune-their-shades-to-attract-bees-even-the-smallest-change-decide-which-genes-survive/articleshow/132518533.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T20:48:05+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132518633,imgsize-234844.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[A human-bred aquarium fish prized for its bright colour has escaped into a Philippines crater lake]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132516374.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Flowerhorn cichlids, bred by humans, have found their way into Lake Sampaloc, a crater lake in the Philippines. Their presence poses a significant threat to the local ecosystem, competing aggressively with native ayungin fish and disrupting aquaculture. Experts raise alarms about the potential for disease transmission and the rapid expansion of this invasive species, underscoring a pressing global issue of domesticated animals affecting natural habitats.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/a-human-bred-aquarium-fish-prized-for-its-bright-colour-and-head-hump-has-escaped-into-a-philippines-crater-lake-where-scientists-fear-it-may-threaten-native-biodiversity/articleshow/132516374.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/a-human-bred-aquarium-fish-prized-for-its-bright-colour-and-head-hump-has-escaped-into-a-philippines-crater-lake-where-scientists-fear-it-may-threaten-native-biodiversity/articleshow/132516374.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T21:10:14+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132518554,imgsize-177934.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Trump scores own-goal as World Cup overflows with politics]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132518683.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/trump-scores-own-goal-as-world-cup-overflows-with-politics/articleshow/132518683.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/trump-scores-own-goal-as-world-cup-overflows-with-politics/articleshow/132518683.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T20:54:27+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Chidanand Rajghatta</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132518714,imgsize-876646.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[A floating 'igloo' research station has left France for Arctic, where it will drift with polar ice]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132515527.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[A floating research station shaped like a giant aluminium igloo has left France on a two-year Arctic mission to study biodiversity and the effects of climate change. The station will drift with sea ice while an international team of scientists collects more than 10,000 samples despite extreme cold, months of darkness and the risk of polar bear encounters.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/a-floating-igloo-research-station-has-left-france-for-the-arctic-where-it-will-drift-with-polar-ice-to-study-climate-change-and-life-in-one-of-earths-harshest-environments/articleshow/132515527.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/rest-of-world/a-floating-igloo-research-station-has-left-france-for-the-arctic-where-it-will-drift-with-polar-ice-to-study-climate-change-and-life-in-one-of-earths-harshest-environments/articleshow/132515527.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T20:07:06+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132516203,imgsize-285590.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Xi's US trip appears on track even as Trump's election interference claims inject fresh strain]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/