s.com/world/us/california-city-manager-arrested-over-alleged-yacht-burglary-weeks-after-taking-office/articleshow/132517503.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/california-city-manager-arrested-over-alleged-yacht-burglary-weeks-after-taking-office/articleshow/132517503.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T19:52:08+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132517589,imgsize-715647.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Scientists marked this coral reef as dead in the 1960s; underwater drones found it alive...]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132516959.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[After being presumed extinct for sixty years, a remarkable coral reef off West Africa has been rediscovered, thriving with an array of fish and coral species. This vibrant mesophotic coral ecosystem thrives in low-light environments beneath the ocean's surface. Researchers speculate that similar hidden reefs could exist along the West African coastline, providing valuable insights into the evolutionary history of the region's marine life and past environmental changes.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-marked-this-west-african-coral-reef-as-probably-dead-in-the-1960s-underwater-drones-found-it-alive-more-than-50-metres-below-the-sea/articleshow/132516959.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/scientists-marked-this-west-african-coral-reef-as-probably-dead-in-the-1960s-underwater-drones-found-it-alive-more-than-50-metres-below-the-sea/articleshow/132516959.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T19:49:04+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132517609,imgsize-239610.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[FedEx CEO Raj Subramaniam grabbed the opportunity that his roommate rejected: He can't come but can I send my resume?]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132517128.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/fedex-ceo-raj-subramaniam-grabbed-the-opportunity-that-his-roommate-rejected-he-cant-come-but-can-i-send-my-resume/articleshow/132517128.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/fedex-ceo-raj-subramaniam-grabbed-the-opportunity-that-his-roommate-rejected-he-cant-come-but-can-i-send-my-resume/articleshow/132517128.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T19:12:23+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132517203,imgsize-523467.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Illinois farmers are making up to $200,000 a year without growing more crops as solar companies offer long-term leases worth up to $2,000 per acre]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132516820.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/illinois-farmers-are-making-up-to-200000-a-year-without-growing-more-crops-as-solar-companies-offer-long-term-leases-worth-up-to-2000-per-acre/articleshow/132516820.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/us/illinois-farmers-are-making-up-to-200000-a-year-without-growing-more-crops-as-solar-companies-offer-long-term-leases-worth-up-to-2000-per-acre/articleshow/132516820.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T19:03:38+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132517034,imgsize-1530920.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Hunters carried trout past waterfalls into fishless Norwegian mountain lakes 7,000 years ago]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132515296.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[In a remarkable feat 7,000 years ago, ancient hunter-gatherers transformed Norwegian mountain lakes by introducing brown trout. Archaeologists discovered remnants of intricate fish traps from 5000 BC, highlighting how these early communities intentionally manipulated their ecosystems for sustainable food resources. They even transported live fish through rugged landscapes, paving the way for the fisheries we know today, where anglers still catch their ancient descendants.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/hunter-gatherers-carried-trout-past-waterfalls-into-fishless-norwegian-mountain-lakes-7000-years-ago-their-descendants-are-still-caught-there-today/articleshow/132515296.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/science/hunter-gatherers-carried-trout-past-waterfalls-into-fishless-norwegian-mountain-lakes-7000-years-ago-their-descendants-are-still-caught-there-today/articleshow/132515296.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T18:19:44+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Science Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132516133,imgsize-247628.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[A couple bought their dream home and got the keys, only to discover the property was a snake habitat after moving in]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132516128.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[Tyler and Lauren Bouldin bought an abandoned historic Pennsylvania home in 2020.  They discovered the neglected grounds had become a thriving habitat for various snakes.  The couple learned to manage the wildlife by making the property less attractive to them.  They safely captured and relocated snakes encountered near their home.  Five years later, the property is transformed into their dream family home.]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/real-estate/news/a-couple-bought-their-dream-home-and-got-the-keys-only-to-discover-the-property-was-a-snake-habitat-after-moving-in/articleshow/132516128.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/real-estate/news/a-couple-bought-their-dream-home-and-got-the-keys-only-to-discover-the-property-was-a-snake-habitat-after-moving-in/articleshow/132516128.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T18:15:19+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI Real Estate Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132516184,imgsize-213502.cms"/></item><item><title><![CDATA[Saudi Arabia launches new one-year, multiple-entry Umrah visa with 90-day stay]]></title><description>&lt;img border="0" hspace="10" align="left" style="margin-top:3px;margin-right:5px;" src="https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/photo/132516106.cms" /&gt;<![CDATA[]]></description><link><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/saudi-arabia-launches-new-one-year-multiple-entry-umrah-visa-with-90-day-stay/articleshow/132516106.cms]]></link><guid><![CDATA[https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/world/middle-east/saudi-arabia-launches-new-one-year-multiple-entry-umrah-visa-with-90-day-stay/articleshow/132516106.cms]]></guid><pubDate>2026-07-20T18:21:42+05:30</pubDate><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">TOI World Desk</dc:creator><enclosure type="image/jpeg" url="https://static.toiimg.com/photo/msid-132516266,imgsize-1575444.cms"/></item><item><title><![C